.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-reconnect - Recover a stale VPN connection


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel reconnect [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Clears stale VPN state and re-authenticates with the AceTeam Network.

.PP
When tsnet state becomes stale (expired/revoked Headscale key, corrupted
WireGuard state), the VPN cannot reconnect. This command automates recovery:
.IP "  1." 5
Verifies VPN is actually broken (exits early if already connected)
.IP "  2." 5
Fetches a fresh authkey using the device API token
.IP "  3." 5
Attempts reconnect with existing state (preserves IP address)
.IP "  4." 5
Falls back to clearing state + fresh connect if needed

.PP
Requires a device API token (stored during 'citadel login' or 'citadel init').

.PP
Use --force to skip the verify step and go straight to clear + reconnect.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Skip verification, clear state and reconnect from scratch

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for reconnect


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Reconnect (tries IP-preserving reconnect first)
  citadel reconnect

  # Force clear state and reconnect from scratch
  citadel reconnect --force
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
